---
// Story 2.5 — the browsable vault index, the site's entry surface at `/`.
//
// Replaces the Story-1.1 "Coming soon" placeholder. The listing is GENERATED
// from the `pages` content collection (NOT a hand-maintained list), so adding a
// `.md` to the vault and rebuilding makes it appear automatically — the
// "add a file, get a page (and it shows up in the index)" promise.
//
// Each entry links to its route via `entry.id` (the authoritative, already
// index-collapsed slug the catch-all emits — `sub/index.md` -> `/sub`), with a
// human-readable label from the SAME title precedence the destination uses.
//
// Decisions (Dev Agent Record):
//  - A: the index lives at `/` by replacing `src/pages/index.astro` (the index
//    is NOT in the `pages` collection, so it never lists itself).
//  - B: a single flat <ul> sorted by route (`entry.id`), CI-stably via a plain
//    code-unit comparison (`a.id < b.id ? -1 : a.id > b.id ? 1 : 0`) — ICU/CLDR-
//    independent, so the order is identical on dev and CI regardless of host
//    locale data (does not depend on `localeCompare` collation).
//  - C: `/` is owned by this page; `content/**/*.md` by `[...slug].astro`. An
//    `entry.id === ''` (a future root `content/index.md`) is filtered out so the
//    index never emits a `/` self-link.
//  - D: label = `entry.data.title || slugToTitle(entry.id)` (the cheap path, no
//    per-entry render()). For an H1-only page (e.g. `/no-h1`) the label is the
//    slug-derived Title Case while the destination <title> is the H1 — a known,
//    documented divergence; `/no-h1` has no H1 either, so its label is "No H1".
//
// Themed via the shared `Page` layout (2.1 shell + 2.2 GitHub theme), JS-free,
// crawlable. This page owns the vault LISTING only; the 2.6 site-header /
// pitch-card / CTA chrome is inherited from `Page.astro` (not rendered here).
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import { buildIndexItems } from '../lib/index-entries.mjs';
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';

const entries = await getCollection('pages');

// Build the sorted listing via the shared pure helper (empty-id filter,
// never-empty label, code-unit sort). Extracted so the empty-vault /
// single-page degenerate branches are unit-testable without an alternate vault.
const items = buildIndexItems(entries);
---

<Page title="The Markdown Web">
  <h1>The Markdown Web</h1>
  {
    items.length === 0 ? (
      <p>No pages yet.</p>
    ) : (
      <ul>
        {items.map((item) => (
          <li>
            <a href={item.href}>{item.label}</a>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    )
  }
</Page>
